1
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,720
Help me pick one out.

2
00:01:21,319 --> 00:01:22,559
Is it for a female client?

3
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:23,400
Yes.

4
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:24,360
For a client.

5
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:26,000
How old is she?

6
00:01:29,559 --> 00:01:30,319
Her age...

7
00:01:30,319 --> 00:01:31,040
About the same as yours.

8
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,440
Just pick one

9
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:33,599
that you like.

10
00:01:35,199 --> 00:01:35,959
One that I like?

11
00:01:37,599 --> 00:01:38,639
You're not giving it to me, are you?

12
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,879
Why are you giving me things again?

13
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:44,680
I just felt that

14
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:47,120
I wasn't nice to you before.

15
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:49,639
And now you're back at work.

16
00:01:50,599 --> 00:01:51,480
Giving you a bag

17
00:01:52,319 --> 00:01:53,360
is just to show my appreciation.

18
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:55,440
I'm sorry.

19
00:01:55,639 --> 00:01:56,239
I have something to do.

20
00:01:56,239 --> 00:01:56,919
I'll get going.

21
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:07,919
Tongzhou Factory.

22
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:10,919
Once it's sold, there's no turning back.

23
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:12,080
No matter what,

24
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,080
we must stop the sale of the factory.

25
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:15,000
Chairman,

26
00:02:15,399 --> 00:02:16,720
do you mean

27
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,279
we use public opinion to blow this up,

28
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,199
and draw the public's attention

29
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,119
to focus on the sale

30
00:02:23,119 --> 00:02:24,399
of the factory?

31
00:02:24,759 --> 00:02:25,639
Director Hu,

32
00:02:26,679 --> 00:02:27,720
mobilize the labor union first,

33
00:02:28,479 --> 00:02:29,960
and have them rally the workers

34
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,199
to protest

35
00:02:34,559 --> 00:02:35,399
against Rosenmoss.

36
00:02:35,639 --> 00:02:36,720
Trust me, everyone.

37
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,919
The company will do everything it can

38
00:02:39,119 --> 00:02:40,199
to save your jobs.

39
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,639
Right now, Rosenmoss

40
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:44,639
is determined to sell the factory.

41
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:46,919
So we all need to work together

42
00:02:47,399 --> 00:02:49,160
to fight against Rosenmoss.

43
00:02:49,639 --> 00:02:50,720
Okay.

44
00:02:51,039 --> 00:02:51,679
Got it?

45
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,240
Can a little negative impact

46
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,600
really decide the factory's fate?

47
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,759
Maybe

48
00:02:58,759 --> 00:03:00,399
it really can make a difference.

49
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:02,639
But this method

50
00:03:03,039 --> 00:03:03,479
is a bit...

51
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:03,919
Let me tell you,

52
00:03:03,919 --> 00:03:04,759
this definitely won't work.

53
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:05,919
What do you mean?

54
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,360
If we want to save the factory,

55
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:09,559
the best way

56
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:11,360
is to let Rosenmoss

57
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:13,160
know our factory's economic value.

58
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:14,839
No company

59
00:03:15,199 --> 00:03:17,279
would push away a profitable factory.

60
00:03:17,279 --> 00:03:17,800
Right, right, right.

61
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,559
You have a point.

62
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:21,000
But right now, we don't even have

63
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:23,399
a channel to talk to Rosenmoss.

64
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,800
Giving designer brands.

65
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:33,919
You messed up, didn't you?

66
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:34,880
Yeah.

67
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,160
Don't be mad.

68
00:03:36,559 --> 00:03:36,919
Well...

69
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:38,600
But... but... this... this...

70
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:39,559
Listen to me.

71
00:03:40,039 --> 00:03:41,440
A girl like Jiaqi...

72
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,960
She might be a bit picky.

73
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:44,919
A girl like her...

74
00:03:44,919 --> 00:03:45,559
She... she...

75
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,479
She focuses more on...

76
00:03:48,119 --> 00:03:49,199
Inner sincerity.

77
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:50,720
She doesn't care much about money.

78
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:52,600
Is there a difference between money and sincerity?

79
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,559
How do you show sincerity without spending money?

80
00:03:54,839 --> 00:03:55,399
Vulgar.

81
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:56,960
No, no, no.

82
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,279
What I mean is...

83
00:03:58,559 --> 00:03:59,080
Jiaqi...

84
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,320
Is a very...

85
00:04:00,839 --> 00:04:01,800
Rare kind of girl.

86
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:02,919
So...

87
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,240
Here, here, here.

88
00:04:12,199 --> 00:04:13,000
Have some water.

89
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,559
So...

90
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,519
For a girl like Jiaqi...

91
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:19,920
Putting in some effort...

92
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,440
Is what you should do.

93
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,239
How about this?

94
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,079
Let's first win over...

95
00:04:25,079 --> 00:04:26,640
Her close friends.

96
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,480
Why?

97
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,000
Haven't you heard?

98
00:04:30,279 --> 00:04:30,760
Well...

99
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:31,920
For girls...

100
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,600
As long as their friends put in a good word for you...

101
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:36,119
The girl will slowly calm down.

102
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:38,200
How about...

103
00:04:42,399 --> 00:04:42,920
We do this.

104
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,760
Let's throw a party.

105
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,359
What party?

106
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,720
Jiaqi's best friends in the company...

107
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,000
Are Peng Weiwei and Yao Shihui.

108
00:04:51,399 --> 00:04:52,519
We can use your moving as an excuse...

109
00:04:52,799 --> 00:04:54,239
And invite them over.

110
00:04:54,799 --> 00:04:55,600
Just say...

111
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,160
It's to...

112
00:04:56,559 --> 00:04:59,040
Thank these hard-working secretaries.

113
00:05:00,279 --> 00:05:01,000
Don't even think about it.

114
00:05:01,799 --> 00:05:03,119
Why would I let strangers into my house?

115
00:05:05,079 --> 00:05:05,959
Here's the thing, boss.

116
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:06,839
You don't know this...

117
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,119
Normal people...

118
00:05:08,119 --> 00:05:09,040
When they move...

119
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:09,920
Will invite friends...

120
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:10,760
Over for a housewarming.

121
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,040
Only their best friends.

122
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,119
So...

123
00:05:13,399 --> 00:05:14,040
If you invite them...

124
00:05:15,279 --> 00:05:17,040
It shows your sincerity.

125
00:05:19,119 --> 00:05:19,679
I won't.

126
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:21,440
Forget it then.

127
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:22,799
Pretend I didn't say anything.

128
00:05:22,799 --> 00:05:23,160
Fine.

129
00:05:23,679 --> 00:05:25,239
She's not giving me attitude anyway.

130
00:05:25,519 --> 00:05:26,799
Why am I worrying about this?

131
00:05:28,239 --> 00:05:29,679
The person involved isn't worried.

132
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:31,880
Wait, wait...

133
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:34,359
Do you guarantee this method works?

134
00:05:36,079 --> 00:05:37,279
It won't backfire, at least.

135
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:47,000
Well,

136
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,359
Labor Day is coming up soon.

137
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:53,239
To reward everyone,

138
00:05:55,239 --> 00:05:56,040
I've prepared

139
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,040
a gift.

140
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:58,920
President Gu,

141
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,399
I didn't expect you to give gifts.

142
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,640
It's not just a gift.

143
00:06:01,959 --> 00:06:02,480
President Gu

144
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,279
feels that

145
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:04,320
the secretaries have been working hard,

146
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:05,640
and he hopes everyone can bond.

147
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,160
He decided to

148
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:07,920
host a

149
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:08,320
housewarming

150
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,200
party

151
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,000
at his place.

152
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:11,679
He hopes all three of you can attend.

153
00:06:11,959 --> 00:06:12,440
Really?

154
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,600
Are we invited?

155
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,040
But let's get this straight first.

156
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,559
I don't lack anything at home.

157
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,399
You don't need to bring me any gifts.

158
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,000
Also,

159
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,399
after you arrive,

160
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:23,399
you can't just touch anything in the house.

161
00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:25,480
What President Gu means is,

162
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,640
he hopes everyone

163
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:27,320
can do him the honor of coming.

164
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,119
Let's see you on Sunday.

165
00:06:29,119 --> 00:06:29,679
Alright?

166
00:06:30,399 --> 00:06:31,040
Well,

167
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:32,279
Weiwei, Shihui,

168
00:06:32,519 --> 00:06:33,640
this weekend,

169
00:06:33,799 --> 00:06:35,519
if you really can't get away,

170
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:36,200
don't force yourselves.

171
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,799
We're fine! We're fine!

172
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:38,959
I have time.

173
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,200
Alright then.

174
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,839
Then let's give a round of applause

175
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,200
for President Gu's

176
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:43,600
housewarming

177
00:06:43,679 --> 00:06:44,160
party!

178
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:46,799
Go!

179
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:47,799
Exactly!

180
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,040
Okay.

181
00:06:49,239 --> 00:06:49,679
Go!

182
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,399
Jiaqi,

183
00:07:00,239 --> 00:07:02,279
where President Gu lives now...

184
00:07:06,239 --> 00:07:07,160
I'll just say halfway through

185
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:07,959
that my friend is sick,

186
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:08,839
and then leave.

187
00:07:09,399 --> 00:07:10,119
Later,

188
00:07:10,119 --> 00:07:11,160
you have to play along with me, okay?

189
00:07:11,359 --> 00:07:12,799
I'll definitely let you leave early.

190
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:13,839
How about

191
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,559
I go buy some fruit?

192
00:07:15,839 --> 00:07:17,079
It's economical and practical.

193
00:07:17,399 --> 00:07:19,079
We can eat it together then.

194
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,519
Alright.

195
00:07:20,799 --> 00:07:21,519
I'll look at some red wine.

196
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,000
Okay then.

197
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Then I'll go buy fruit.

198
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:40,519
Hello.

199
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:41,320
Zi'ang.

200
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:43,119
Are you busy?

201
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:44,799
I need you to do me a favor.

202
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:46,959
Jiaqi.

203
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,320
Are you sick?

204
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,760
Why does your voice sound hoarse?

205
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:51,760
It's fine.

206
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,359
Drinking some hot water will do.

207
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,119
By the way,

208
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:56,600
what did you need me for?

209
00:07:58,640 --> 00:07:59,359
It's nothing.

210
00:08:00,679 --> 00:08:01,640
You can't just drink water.

211
00:08:02,239 --> 00:08:03,040
How about this?

212
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,160
I'll buy some medicine

213
00:08:04,239 --> 00:08:05,079
and bring it over to you.

214
00:08:06,239 --> 00:08:06,760
Okay.

215
00:08:07,799 --> 00:08:08,559
See you later.

216
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,399
The air here is so fresh.

217
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,160
Yeah.

218
00:08:18,359 --> 00:08:18,920
Come.

219
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,760
Please, come in. Come in.

220
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,200
President Gu.

221
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,200
Just a small token

222
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:23,959
of our appreciation.

223
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:24,679
Congratulations on your new home.

224
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,160
Didn't I say no gifts were needed?

225
00:08:29,079 --> 00:08:30,119
Thank you. Thank you. Thanks.

226
00:08:30,359 --> 00:08:30,959
Well, President Gu

227
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:32,039
just didn't want you to spend money.

228
00:08:34,799 --> 00:08:35,880
So much delicious food.

229
00:08:36,239 --> 00:08:37,559
We're going to gain weight today.

230
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:40,599
Look.

231
00:08:41,119 --> 00:08:42,599
This house is really nice.

232
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,559
When will we ever be able to afford one?

233
00:08:45,119 --> 00:08:45,679
Um,

234
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:47,359
is Secretary Lin not here?

235
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,119
She said she had something to do.

236
00:08:50,119 --> 00:08:51,200
She'll be here in a bit.

237
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:52,599
Come, have a seat.

238
00:08:52,599 --> 00:08:52,880
Sit.

239
00:08:53,039 --> 00:08:53,359
Sit.

240
00:08:53,559 --> 00:08:53,799
Sit.

241
00:08:54,119 --> 00:08:54,520
Sit.

242
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:55,440
Look over there.

243
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:17,039
I bought you some cold medicine and fever reducers.

244
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,359
You should take them right away.

245
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:28,760
Oh my god.

246
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:29,520
You're burning up.

247
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,239
You need to take the medicine right now.

248
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:32,960
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

249
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,520
Am I dreaming?

250
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:44,479
Peng Weiwei?

251
00:09:44,719 --> 00:09:45,320
Stop drinking.

252
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,000
You'll feel sick if you drink too much.

253
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,320
Come on.

254
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:49,520
Cheers.

255
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:53,039
Secretary Lin

256
00:09:53,039 --> 00:09:54,119
sent a message saying

257
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,719
something came up for her today.

258
00:09:56,719 --> 00:09:58,159
She has to go somewhere else.

259
00:09:58,159 --> 00:09:59,919
She hopes we have fun.

260
00:09:59,919 --> 00:10:00,520
What?

261
00:10:02,119 --> 00:10:02,719
Is she playing me?

262
00:10:07,479 --> 00:10:08,080
Do you think

263
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:10,479
it's because of this house

264
00:10:10,919 --> 00:10:12,159
that she didn't want to come?

265
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:16,559
I think you have a point.

266
00:10:17,119 --> 00:10:18,280
What are you two whispering about?

267
00:10:22,119 --> 00:10:23,400
Tell me.

268
00:10:24,919 --> 00:10:26,320
Actually, this house

269
00:10:26,599 --> 00:10:28,080
is the one Jiaqi's fiance

270
00:10:28,599 --> 00:10:29,919
had his eye on before he died.

271
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,799
They originally wanted to save up

272
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,479
to buy this house.

273
00:10:33,719 --> 00:10:34,559
But now... Wait.

274
00:10:35,679 --> 00:10:36,640
Died?

275
00:10:38,119 --> 00:10:38,840
That guy died?

276
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:39,679
Yeah.

277
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,440
He was also a family member

278
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:42,479
of a Feimanchi employee.

279
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:45,080
He died in a car crash a while ago.

280
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:46,359
The hit-and-run driver

281
00:10:46,599 --> 00:10:47,640
still hasn't been found.

282
00:10:48,239 --> 00:10:49,440
Leaving Jiaqi all alone.

283
00:10:49,599 --> 00:10:50,599
What is she going to do?

284
00:10:50,679 --> 00:10:51,479
Besides,

285
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,080
this house

286
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,080
was a promise between him and Jiaqi.

287
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,200
They were definitely going to buy it.

288
00:10:58,599 --> 00:10:59,280
Now,

289
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:00,760
Jiaqi

290
00:11:01,119 --> 00:11:02,640
doesn't want to come over.

291
00:11:08,359 --> 00:11:09,039
Are you okay?

292
00:11:10,599 --> 00:11:11,960
Did Curly suddenly call off the wedding

293
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:12,840
and dump you?

294
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:14,520
The first time I saw him,

295
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,640
I knew he was unreliable.

296
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,280
People like him

297
00:11:17,359 --> 00:11:17,880
should just...

298
